      <p>Our 12-bedroom facility opened in 2019, built with the support of our community, and designed to feel like a home rather than an institution.</p>
      <h2>Inside the shelter</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Shared sitting areas, a kitchen, and a dining area</li>
        <li>Children's play areas</li>
        <li>A range of bedroom configurations for individuals and families</li>
        <li>ADA-accessible bathrooms and common spaces</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="callout">
        <p>For the safety of everyone staying with us, our shelter's exact location is kept confidential — the photos here are representative of the space rather than identifying specific rooms or the building's location.</p>
